22/05/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Bulgaria's Interior Minister Georgi Petkanov and Greek Minister of Public Order Giorgos Voulgarakis agreed to increase co-operation in the police sector, during a visit by Petkanov to Athens on Friday (20 May). 
The ministers stressed the need for stepping up joint efforts in the fight against human and drug trafficking, illegal migration and money counterfeiting.
In separate news, the Bulgarian Interior Ministry announced Friday that Italian authorities have detained a Macedonian Albanian with a Bulgarian passport, Metush Bajrami, said to be one of the bosses of the drug trafficking network in the Balkans. 
Bajrami, 47, was arrested near Milan. 
(MPA, BNR - 20/05/05)
